
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-lear-dhc-timezone-option-02.txt'>
    <title>"A Timezone Option for DHCP", Paul Eggert, Eliot Lear</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-lear-dhc-timezone-option-02.txt</link>
    <description>DHCP defines an option for a server to deliver to a client offset from UTC. This information in and of itself is not sufficient for devices to portray local time both accurately and consistently. This memo specifies a new option for both DHCPv4 and DHCPv6 to do so.</description>
    <dc:date>2006-03-06T08:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
